Interface CustomResource

All Known Subinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractCustomResource
public interface CustomResource
extends Resource, Identifiable, TimeStamped

Interface for a Resource that is not portal managed, thus called a custom resource. It is identified by the URI and a ObjectID will be created for this custom resource when it is created. This ObjectID can only be used within the ResourceModel or the TagModel or RatingModel to search for a custom resource.
Note:It is important to implement the Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() methods as custom resource likely are held in collections.

Since:
7.0.0
Note:
This interface is designed to be implemented by clients.
